      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> columnar <rs type="objectType"><rs type="objectType">statue base</rs> shaft</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">1.67</measure>, diam.
<measure dim="diameter" unit="metre" type="length">0.48</measure>) with a moulded upper rim; the stone is badly weathered, and
partly broken away above.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> very lightly on the upper part of the column.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Elongated; av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.05</measure>, <term lang="grc-Latn">phi</term> <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.06</measure>; standard <term lang="grc-Latn">sigma</term> and <term lang="grc-Latn">omega</term>;
the style appears appropriate to the late third or early fourth
century. Boulanger apparently saw traces of red paint in the letters, but
none remains.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p>c. <date notAfter="0350" exact="both" precision="circa" notBefore="0324">A.D. 324-350</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>, <rs type="criteria">content</rs>).</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
<ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" key="agty" full="yes"><w lemma="ἀγαθός">Ἀγαθῇ</w> <w lemma="τύχη">Τύχῃ</w></persName><lb n="2"/><persName key="FlZeno" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Φλάβιος"><expan><abbr>Φλ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">άουιος</supplied></expan></name> <name reg="Ζήνων">Ζήνων</name></persName> <rs type="official-relig" key="highpriest"><w lemma="ἀρχιερεύς"><del status="unremarkable"><unclear reason="damage">ἀρχ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ιε</supplied></del><lb n="3" type="worddiv"/><supplied reason="lost"><del status="unremarkable">ρεὺς</del></supplied></w></rs> <supplied reason="lost"><del status="unremarkable"><w lemma="καί">καὶ</w></del></supplied> <rs type="dignity" key="comes"><w lemma="κόμης">κόμης</w></rs><lb n="4"/><w lemma="ποιέω">ἐποίει</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέ<lb n="5" type="worddiv"/>θηκεν</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῇ</w> <w lemma="πατρίς">πα<lb n="6" type="worddiv"/>τρίδι</w> <g type="leaf"/>
</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="apparatus">
        <head>Apparatus</head>
        <p>l. 2, The first three erased letters remain legible; the rest can safely be resored by comparison with text <xref type="inscription" n="12" href="050302">5.302</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>With Good Fortune. Fl<supplied reason="abbreviation">avius</supplied> Zenon <supplied reason="lost">high priest and</supplied>
<seg cert="low">comes</seg>, made <supplied reason="subaudible">this</supplied> and set it up for his
homeland.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>For Flavius Zenon see also  <xref type="inscription" n="12" href="050302">5.302</xref> and
discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="II.25">II.25</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p> <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList" key="HadrBath">Hadrianic Baths, East Court</rs>: '<foreign lang="fr">face E<supplied reason="abbreviation">st</supplied> du pilier
N<supplied reason="abbreviation">ord</supplied></foreign>' (Boulanger).</rs> <rs type="origLocation">Unknown.</rs> <rs type="lastLocation"><rs type="monuList" key="HadrBath">Hadrianic Baths, East Court</rs>: among pieces assembled from French excavations (1994).</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Excavated by <rs type="visitor" key="boulanger">Boulanger</rs>, <date value="1913" notBefore="1913" notAfter="1913" exact="both">16 October 1913</date> (notebook A, 71,
whence B, 37); recorded by the NYU expedition.</p>
      </div>

